reviews.text: Great coffee. Seating area a bit tight but outdoor area is nice when the weather is good

It's a very nice space, but the acoustics are really bad when there is an event with a full house.  Also the lady manager on duty they night I was there, was rude and condescending when we were leaving - on time.  No cheery good humour or Happy Christmas from her.  There are other venues - seek them out before you book St Peters

St. Peters is a beautiful venue, hidden in the middle of Cork city. The regular markets and events here are always worth a visit and the cafe is wonderful, with excellent staff. Always worth a quick stop, you may stay longer than you intended!
Well recommended if you enjoy an airy gallery with plenty of works to delight photography and art fans

I believe this Church is the oldest in Cork, dating back to medieval time when the City was walled and surrounded by rivers, marshes and islands. It's been refurbished, modernised inside, has exhibitions, friendly helpful staff and small but very tasty coffee shop. If you visit you might see me there.

Fantastic place to visit while in Cork City, so much history. Easy 5-10 minute walk from the centre. Next to Saint Finbarres Cathedral. 

Free entry, wonderful views and photo opportunities. 

There's a guided tour at 1pm each day for a small charge of €3 which I highly recommend.

Our guide Steve was knowledgeable, informative and added a bit of humour too! :)
A very nice place to visit. Its very well preserved and maintained. A contact with history and in same time a great view over Cork City area.
I love the continuity of governance from 1600 to now. Still had a working Garda station inside it. Free entry and free guided tours. Worth a visit

We had a brilliant time there. Steve was our guide on the tour around the fort and made it so interesting. He gave us lots of background information that we wouldn't have gotten in any other way and was just so funny. You get stunning views of the city and can travel back in different periods of times. Would do it again.

This place was a nice little stop in October 2017, as it was a Garda station closed to the public when I was there last (2005).  Nice views of the city and nearby cathedral and some interesting little historical tidbits too.  It was free to wander the walls when we visited.

Absolutely lovely cathedral to visit. Staff is always extremely friendly and helpful. The price (5-6€) is so reasonable compared to many lesser cathedrals in ireland. Worth visiting whether you're religious or not. The second time we visited, they were 5 minutes late to open and gave us one ticket for free as a courtesy. We love to visit saint fin barres and recommend it to anyone who's visiting cork.

Beautiful. Amazing. Tranquil. The labyrinth was my favorite since the church had a service at the time I showed up and could not explore inside the cathedral. But it was still nostalgic to hear kids singing bible versus. Reminded me of when I was a kid.

Great place to stop by and read the history of the Cathedral when visiting County Cork, they have one of or the largest  pipe organs in the world I forgot how many pieces total but it's a high number. The grounds are beautifully kept and it's a great place to take pictures.
Very nice cathedral. The organ is unique in its kind. The staff is really friendly. Don't forget to visit the outside area and labyrinth. I really enjoyed my visit

If you like magnificent Cathedrals then you must visit St Fin Barre's. Entrance fee of 5Euro, I think, and if you smile nicely and ask for a guide then it's history, stories and features come alive. And if you manage to catch a service and choir it just adds the cream. Explore and enjoy.

Overall, it was an okay experience. The cafe was aesthetically pleasing and the staff were lovely. It was 1:15pm so it was a real shock to find out that they were only serving the brunch menu at that time. We had to wait 20 minutes for 2 slices of toast, and the food was cold. I was quite disappointed as I was expecting more from such a beautiful cafe.

A great art gallery and an amazing use of space. Close to the city it offers food and coffee and a space to reflect or catch up with friends. Free entry so another reason to visit. Nice gift shop too. Kid friendly.
Excelent artsy museum, hosting lots of craft fairs.

Concept? Great. Location? Great. Actual value add to arts scene ?... unproven. Surely even UCC itself has dozens of artists and they'll never see the inside of the gallery. Pretentious,  empty and seems to be no more than an excuse to have a cafe downstairs and presumably a big day for a donor
Bold design architecture, innovative art displays, complete experience, with screening room and book shop, surrounded by beautiful environment.

We have been on two tours. One in 2016 with Jack and most recently in June 2017 with Michael. Both guys were great. Very friendly and knowledgeable. The two tours took in different areas of the city which made the second just as interesting as the first. You get to see places you might never have known were there. A great way to see Cork and get in some walking as well. Both guys had their recommendations for places to see and where to go for great food. 
Highly recommended.
Great

Attended a conference. Found the food excellent and the facilities were not bad. Very annoying that some of our clients who went out for some air were not able to enter due to the automatic doors being locked. The security guard was not there and when he finally came back was a bit rude.

My first time was when Liam Miller tribute game of Manchester United legends v Celtic & Ireland Legends. Very impressed with the stadium. Very clean and well looked after. Never been to a GAA game here yet but I'm sure fine place. Hot and cold food served in the restaurant inside up to date stadium right near Cork city so easy walk to here. Fine views from here too.
The business rooms great with a view of the astroturf pitches and the food catered for our sales kickoff was amazing.
Very up to date and modern rest station. The statue of the Obamas is very well done also. Clean toilets and a large varies selection of hot and cold meals. Well worth stopping at
The pitch was in very poor condition, the game shouldn't have been played on it. I left feeling that the management didn't consider the safety of the players or the enjoyment of their patrons

There's a guided tour at 1pm each day for a small charge of €3 which I highly recommend.

Our guide Steve was knowledgeable, informative and added a bit of humour too! :)

Would do it again.

Who knew Cork has the best food and service combination in Europe by far!?! UNCLE PETE'S though is a very unique restaurant in the fact that 80/90% of the menu is gluten free and tastes and had texture that surpasses gluten containing food. I had a locally sourced Cider with a meat feast pizza that was nothing short of amazing. The cheesecake flavoured with Baileys and chocolate was great. As was the Rhubarb Pie, that was gluten free too with a pastry that was gorgeous. The service was efficient and friendly. I am going to be back in Ireland and in Cork as the food, the drink and the atmosphere is the best in Europe

I ordered the following for me and my wife 
One pepperoni pizza
One side of chips
Two cokes

Not to much of a fan of the pizza, it was a bit soggy and generally over cooked on the top.

I wouldn’t recommend the pepperoni pizza but some of the other items that people were ordering (like the spaghetti and the desserts) looked great.

The atmosphere was pretty cool.

Wouldn’t recommend the pizza but definitely try some of the other options.

AMAZING. The pizza they serve is not like the pizza you find back in the USA or Canada. This is the kind of traditional pizza they would serve in Italy. I don’t usually like thin crust but this pizza was worth it. The right amount of cheesy. My boyfriend is delighted that it’s called “Uncle Pete” because that’s his name and he’s an uncle to the sweetest toddler that we visited with while in Ireland. I highly recommend tasting the pizza here.
Love this place! Wonderful pizza, excellent food, nice staff, good prices.
best pizza i ever had!!! great staff too

Place so great that I wanted to come back there before I left. Perfect, delicious chicken coconut soup that surprised me with flavours, this soup is just top class.
Red curry, I choose duck from range of meat, was also delicious, if you're chilli head you might feel their "hot" as a mild or mild-medium but aromas makes this dish really tasty and beautiful. Oh, and they have the chopsticks. Truly recommended West from Cork.
Fantastic variety of food from all Asia not just Thailand. The quality of the food is fantastic, service is friendly and efficient. Price is extremely fair.

First time for a long time. Starter was a bit scarce. The main dish was enough. Mine was Nasi Goren but although the fried rice and the chicken was a normal one (normal, that you could fine similar ones at other Oriental restaurant, not in the sense of mean), that fried crusty egg on top with the still liquid yolk mixing with the fried onions/rice/chicken, put a really nice different touch to the dish.

Very authentic and delicious Thai restaurant. One of the best I've been to outside of Thailand. Staff are friendly and the menu, although relatively small, is quite reasonably priced. Nice selection of beers too. Would definitely recommend.
Delicious food great service reasonably priced

Fresh good quality produce available. Various little shops like tasty well priced cakes. Delicious sausage rolls freshly made. Good coffee shop upstairs. Fresh juices and smoothies and a newly added sushi shop.

If you like Artisan foods, this is the place for you. You can eat on the go here also. Mind the live lobsters, apparently they do not like camera flash, it could be fatal !!                             Easy located on the South mall, it has several entrances/exits.
Lovely market, great fruit and vegetables. Lovely meat and fresh fish. Great deals. Nice restaurant's. Local producers and international products. A must if you are living or visiting.
What an amazing experience. I haven't seen a meat market of that magnitude before. If you enjoy meat, this is the place to shop!! Also nice veggies with an assortment of fruits, etc as well.

This is a nice spot to walk around even if your not buying anything. They sell everything from meat to fish and even tripe and drisheen.  For people not born in Ireland that may be looking for something that they eat in there country,  this is the place to try.  There is also a cafe upstairs if you need a break or a sit down . They have a great selection of nuts, fruits ,  fancy chocolate and more.  There is also a few shops like a jewellers a hairdressers etc.

Hands down the best vegetarian meal I've ever had. Couldn't recommend the place highly enough. The atmosphere was lovely. The staff were absolutely exceptional. We also stayed in the accommodation which was amazing as well. 10/10 in every regard, can't wait to come back soon!
The best vegetarian restaurant in the country and my favorite restaurant full stop. A real dining experience. Great staff and food
If you want something incredible special this is where to go. Simple as...

I'm not a vegetarian, I'm a carnivore and I've in the past waved away suggestions of going to a vegetarian restaurant. Childish and misinformed - I'm aware of that - we are all but human. Visited Paradiso recently with some friends - every single dish was fantastic. My wife is, by her own admission, not a very adventurous eater was blown away by the quality of the food and finished every single dish. The wine choices are top notch too.

EDIT: Ate here again last Saturday - everything was just as good as my first review. The only thing that had improved was our waiter - such a joy to have someone so enthusiastic and knowledgeable about his work. We nearly had to chase him into the kitchen to take the well-deserved tip!

Cannot recommend this place highly enough.
According to reviews you'd expect five stars for this wonderful vegetarian stalwart, the reality is that it struggled to get a four from me. Still fabulous though - give them a visit!

Exceptional experience! I booked our table for 3 about 6 weeks in advance and was very excited to come here. The atmosphere was so relaxed and the attentive service was so nice and also explained a lot about what was served and where it came from. The menu includes local food and changes every few weeks. Each dish was a perfection .
Really enjoyed the dining experience. The quality of food was matched by the fantastic staff. Thanks Vivienne and company

Fantastic from opening the door to leaving.
Thought has gone into everything from food to ambience and decor.
Don't be surprised if people take a while coming back from toilet. It is amazing.
Food varied and full of taste. Tasting menu but all explained by man himself!!!
( One note get counter or main room if you can. People on small tables didn't look like they were having fun...)

The place is beautiful and well distributed. I consider myself a picky eater of choice but this place made me discover that even the if the ingredients on a regular way of cooking, I don't like it, there is another way to make it more interesting and tasty. I love the idea of cooking with seasonal foods. 

I was fascinated by the attention of the waiter, everything was explained and it was a great experience to eat the food the way the chef wants it to be eaten.

I would love to do it again on another season, to see what else the chef can offer with different ingredients from that season.

Ichigo Ichie is an experience I will never forget. The staff and service was excellent. Very friendly and chatted us up. Gave excellent recommendations for places to go later in the evening and the rest of our trip to Cork. The craft is divine, the presentation was gorgeous, the explanations were thoughtful, and the decor of the establishment was clean and cool. I would highly recommend this experience to anybody. Even if you are unsure, just take the chance. If you're thinking about it, you can afford it. Each serving was delectable and any drink from their menu will pair perfectly.

The food was delicious and they have a nice selection of wine, beer, and spirits. I had the fixed price menu with poached salmon, bacon rib (a rib cut pork chop cured like bacon) and their chocolate cake with hazelnut. The service was polite and friendly but it was a bit slow the day I visited. It's a bit on the expensive side but worth the price. A good experience overall.
First time here. Wonderful place  with a comprehensive Menu to please everyone. Food and Service first class.
Very nice meal. Amazing value. The staff were very attentive and you were well taken care of

I'm still too full to write a thorough review. Let me just say, walk, don't run to have a delicious dining experience. Vegans, trust me,this is an extremely vegan friendly omnivore restaurant. The service is first class. We will be back
Ambiance was good but food is too salty. Nice blue cheese appetiser though

Very friendly and accommodating staff. Being able to bring your own wine and not pay corkage is a big plus. I had a reservation for 7:30 and dropped my wine in at 5 and the staff kindly obliged by putting it in the fridge so it was chilled for the dinner.

Unbelievable. First-time i ordered vegetarian rolls and got chicken. I thought mistakes can happen but secound time i ordered and payed for a 2l coke and they forgot it.
Twice i ordered and both times they made big 'mistakes'.
Never again.
Great food reasonable price would recommend

I’m for certain you would have been to better Chinese restaurants. I was the only customer eating in this evening which was fine. The radio was on as background music and presentable I guess. The waiter was lovely and sat me down promptly to take my order while guarding the door. There is a lot selection to order from. The plate I was given was hot but had crud on it and one side slight oily. I don’t was happy with the sweet and sour chicken Hong Kong style with fried rice. However, my vegetable spring roll was not done right - one side was very soggy while the other crisp. 

I decided to eat in not a takeaway, my food felt like it was prepared in a very rushed manner. I was full nonetheless. I told the waiter but she still charged me and I wasn’t in a mood to get a couple of euros off my bill. This is definitely a fast food place instead. Thanks!
Love phoenix house nice polite staff and lovely food

Absolutely one of the best restaurants we have ever been too, worldwide.

Location was very delightful, staff was friendly, attentive, acknowledgeable about the menu.

Had to bread appetizer, which had two great sauces: beet and pesto. 

The Hake fish an amazing taste, great sauce, and the side beats were crispy and uniquely done.

My friend had the bacon shoulder, with sides, also done exquisitely well.

Desert: Cake and strawberry meringue, great ending!

Beautiful restaurant with excellent food and service. Knowledgeable, friendly waiter, made the whole dining experience even more enjoyable. 
The food itself was outstanding fresh and flavourful, would have happily eaten the meal AGAIN, if I'd had room.

Had a wonderful lunch here, the staff are friendly and attentive and the food superb. I had the French onion soup and the bacon collar, which was so tender and melt in the mouth. Washed down with a pint of their house stout! So many things on the menu that I wanted to try the only problem you'll have is deciding what to eat. Highly recommended if you are in Cork!

We had sirloin steak. Very nice. Cooked perfectly. The chips were lovely too. We chose peppercorn sauce which was quite disappointing. It was an absolutely tiny serving of very watery, not peppery, brown broth. The staff though, were really friendly and efficient. Will definitely be back. I'll try a different sauce for my gorgeous steak next time. :)

We had reservations on a weeknight and were promptly seated as soon as we arrived, even though we were a few minutes late. 

The food was tasty and the portions were reasonable for the price. My only complaint would be that our server seemed to disappear at the end of the evening before we could request the bill so we ended up staying a bit longer than we intended while we waited for someone to help us get our bill and pay.
